biCPA
=====

Simulator of the scheduling heuristic published in "A Bi-Criteria Algorithm for 
Scheduling Parallel Task Graphs on Clusters. In 10th IEEE/ACM International 
Symposium on Cluster, Cloud and Grid Computing (CCGrid 2010)"

Requires SimGrid (version 3.9 or earlier):
* http://simgrid.gforge.inria.fr
* http://simgrid.gforge.inria.fr/download.html
* 101 tutorial on the used SimDAG API:
  * http://simgrid.gforge.inria.fr/tutorials/101/simdag-101.pdf

The command line accepts three parameters:
* --platform <platform file>: the description of the targer cluster in the
                              simgrid format
* --dag <file>: description of a Parallel Task Graph in the DOT format. Such 
                files can be generated by the daggen tool 
                (https://github.com/frs69wq/daggen)
* --with-communications: This optional parameter impacts the way the (time x 
                         resource) area taken by a task is computed. See the 
                         article for further details.

Examples of platform and dag files are available in the input/ directory.

Typical command line:
./biCPA --platform input/cluster.xml --dag input/daggen_ptg.dot 

Corresponding output:

0.001:0.026:biCPA-M:input/cluster.xml:input/daggen_ptg.dot:202.760:2571.792:20
0.001:0.026:biCPA-E:input/cluster.xml:input/daggen_ptg.dot:202.760:2571.792:20
0.001:0.026:biCPA-S:input/cluster.xml:input/daggen_ptg.dot:202.760:2571.792:20
0.001:0.026:biCPA-W:input/cluster.xml:input/daggen_ptg.dot:213.827:2488.744:19
*****:*****:  CPA  :input/cluster.xml:input/daggen_ptg.dot:218.630:3241.080:20

The format of each output line is:
* allocation time
* mapping time
* Heuristic name
* platform file
* dag file
* makespan
* work (time x resource area)
* peak resource usage

To obtain more verbose outputs add to the command line:
* Full logging
  --log=biCPA.thresh:verbose or --log=biCPA.thresh:debug
* Logging for functions related to a specific element (task, workstations, ...)
   --log=task.thresh:debug

